\title{Modern Python}

\taxon{skill}

\meta{description}{Configures Python projects with modern tooling (uv, ruff, ty). Use when creating projects, writing standalone scripts, or migrating from pip/Poetry/mypy/black.}

\subtree{
\title{Modern Python}
\p{Guide for modern Python tooling and best practices, based on [trailofbits/cookiecutter-python](https://github.com/trailofbits/cookiecutter-python).}

\subtree{
\title{When to Use This Skill}
\ul{
\li{Creating a new Python project or package}
\li{Setting up \code{\startverb pyproject.toml\stopverb} configuration}
\li{Configuring development tools (linting, formatting, testing)}
\li{Writing Python scripts with external dependencies}
\li{Migrating from legacy tools (when user requests it)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{When NOT to Use This Skill}
\ul{
\li{\strong{User wants to keep legacy tooling}: Respect existing workflows if explicitly requested}
\li{\strong{Python < 3.11 required}: These tools target modern Python}
\li{\strong{Non-Python projects}: Mixed codebases where Python isn't primary}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Anti-Patterns to Avoid}
\pre{\startverb
| Avoid | Use Instead |
|-------|-------------|
| `[tool.ty]` python-version | `[tool.ty.environment]` python-version |
| `uv pip install` | `uv add` and `uv sync` |
| Editing pyproject.toml manually to add deps | `uv add <pkg>` / `uv remove <pkg>` |
| `hatchling` build backend | `uv_build` (simpler, sufficient for most cases) |
| Poetry | uv (faster, simpler, better ecosystem integration) |
| requirements.txt | PEP 723 for scripts, pyproject.toml for projects |
| mypy / pyright | ty (faster, from Astral team) |
| `[project.optional-dependencies]` for dev tools | `[dependency-groups]` (PEP 735) |
| Manual virtualenv activation (`source .venv/bin/activate`) | `uv run <cmd>` |
| pre-commit | prek (faster, no Python runtime needed) |
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Key principles:}}

\ul{
\li{Always use \code{\startverb uv add\stopverb} and \code{\startverb uv remove\stopverb} to manage dependencies}
\li{Never manually activate or manage virtual environments—use \code{\startverb uv run\stopverb} for all commands}
\li{Use \code{\startverb [dependency-groups]\stopverb} for dev/test/docs dependencies, not \code{\startverb [project.optional-dependencies]\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Decision Tree}
\pre{\startverb
What are you doing?
│
├─ Single-file script with dependencies?
│   └─ Use PEP 723 inline metadata (./references/pep723-scripts.md)
│
├─ New multi-file project (not distributed)?
│   └─ Minimal uv setup (see Quick Start below)
│
├─ New reusable package/library?
│   └─ Full project setup (see Full Setup below)
│
└─ Migrating existing project?
    └─ See Migration Guide below
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Tool Overview}
\pre{\startverb
| Tool | Purpose | Replaces |
|------|---------|----------|
| **uv** | Package/dependency management | pip, virtualenv, pip-tools, pipx, pyenv |
| **ruff** | Linting AND formatting | flake8, black, isort, pyupgrade, pydocstyle |
| **ty** | Type checking | mypy, pyright (faster alternative) |
| **pytest** | Testing with coverage | unittest |
| **prek** | Pre-commit hooks ([setup](./references/prek.md)) | pre-commit (faster, Rust-native) |
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{Security Tools}
\pre{\startverb
| Tool | Purpose | When It Runs |
|------|---------|--------------|
| **shellcheck** | Shell script linting | pre-commit |
| **detect-secrets** | Secret detection | pre-commit |
| **actionlint** | Workflow syntax validation | pre-commit, CI |
| **zizmor** | Workflow security audit | pre-commit, CI |
| **pip-audit** | Dependency vulnerability scanning | CI, manual |
| **Dependabot** | Automated dependency updates | scheduled |
\stopverb}

\p{See [security-setup.md](./references/security-setup.md) for configuration and usage.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Start: Minimal Project}
\p{For simple multi-file projects not intended for distribution:}

\pre{\startverb
# Create project with uv
uv init myproject
cd myproject

# Add dependencies
uv add requests rich

# Add dev dependencies
uv add --group dev pytest ruff ty

# Run code
uv run python src/myproject/main.py

# Run tools
uv run pytest
uv run ruff check .
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Full Project Setup}
\p{If starting from scratch, ask the user if they prefer to use the Trail of Bits cookiecutter template to bootstrap a complete project with already preconfigured tooling.}

\pre{\startverb
uvx cookiecutter gh:trailofbits/cookiecutter-python
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{1. Create Project Structure}
\pre{\startverb
uv init --package myproject
cd myproject
\stopverb}

\p{This creates:}

\pre{\startverb
myproject/
├── pyproject.toml
├── README.md
├── src/
│   └── myproject/
│       └── __init__.py
└── .python-version
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{2. Configure pyproject.toml}
\p{See [pyproject.md](./references/pyproject.md) for complete configuration reference.}

\p{Key sections:}

\pre{\startverb
[project]
name = "myproject"
version = "0.1.0"
requires-python = ">=3.11"
dependencies = []

[dependency-groups]
dev = [{include-group = "lint"}, {include-group = "test"}, {include-group = "audit"}]
lint = ["ruff", "ty"]
test = ["pytest", "pytest-cov"]
audit = ["pip-audit"]

[tool.ruff]
line-length = 100
target-version = "py311"

[tool.ruff.lint]
select = ["ALL"]
ignore = ["D", "COM812", "ISC001"]

[tool.pytest]
addopts = ["--cov=myproject", "--cov-fail-under=80"]

[tool.ty.terminal]
error-on-warning = true

[tool.ty.environment]
python-version = "3.11"

[tool.ty.rules]
# Strict from day 1 for new projects
possibly-unresolved-reference = "error"
unused-ignore-comment = "warn"
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{3. Install Dependencies}
\pre{\startverb
# Install all dependency groups
uv sync --all-groups

# Or install specific groups
uv sync --group dev
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{4. Add Makefile}
\pre{\startverb
.PHONY: dev lint format test build

dev:
	uv sync --all-groups

lint:
	uv run ruff format --check && uv run ruff check && uv run ty check src/

format:
	uv run ruff format .

test:
	uv run pytest

build:
	uv build
\stopverb}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Migration Guide}
\p{When a user requests migration from legacy tooling:}

\subtree{
\title{From requirements.txt + pip}
\p{First, determine the nature of the code:}

\p{\strong{For standalone scripts}: Convert to PEP 723 inline metadata (see [pep723-scripts.md](./references/pep723-scripts.md))}

\p{\strong{For projects}:}

\pre{\startverb
# Initialize uv in existing project
uv init --bare

# Add dependencies using uv (not by editing pyproject.toml)
uv add requests rich  # add each package

# Or import from requirements.txt (review each package before adding)
# Note: Complex version specifiers may need manual handling
grep -v '^#' requirements.txt | grep -v '^-' | grep -v '^\s*$' | while read -r pkg; do
    uv add "$pkg" || echo "Failed to add: $pkg"
done

uv sync
\stopverb}

\p{Then:}

\ol{
\li{Delete \code{\startverb requirements.txt\stopverb}, \code{\startverb requirements-dev.txt\stopverb}}
\li{Delete virtual environment (\code{\startverb venv/\stopverb}, \code{\startverb .venv/\stopverb})}
\li{Add \code{\startverb uv.lock\stopverb} to version control}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{From setup.py / setup.cfg}
\ol{
\li{Run \code{\startverb uv init --bare\stopverb} to create pyproject.toml}
\li{Use \code{\startverb uv add\stopverb} to add each dependency from \code{\startverb install_requires\stopverb}}
\li{Use \code{\startverb uv add --group dev\stopverb} for dev dependencies}
\li{Copy non-dependency metadata (name, version, description, etc.) to \code{\startverb [project]\stopverb}}
\li{Delete \code{\startverb setup.py\stopverb}, \code{\startverb setup.cfg\stopverb}, \code{\startverb MANIFEST.in\stopverb}}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{From flake8 + black + isort}
\ol{
\li{Remove flake8, black, isort via \code{\startverb uv remove\stopverb}}
\li{Delete \code{\startverb .flake8\stopverb}, \code{\startverb pyproject.toml [tool.black]\stopverb}, \code{\startverb [tool.isort]\stopverb} configs}
\li{Add ruff: \code{\startverb uv add --group dev ruff\stopverb}}
\li{Add ruff configuration (see [ruff-config.md](./references/ruff-config.md))}
\li{Run \code{\startverb uv run ruff check --fix .\stopverb} to apply fixes}
\li{Run \code{\startverb uv run ruff format .\stopverb} to format}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{From mypy / pyright}
\ol{
\li{Remove mypy/pyright via \code{\startverb uv remove\stopverb}}
\li{Delete \code{\startverb mypy.ini\stopverb}, \code{\startverb pyrightconfig.json\stopverb}, or \code{\startverb [tool.mypy]\stopverb}/\code{\startverb [tool.pyright]\stopverb} sections}
\li{Add ty: \code{\startverb uv add --group dev ty\stopverb}}
\li{Run \code{\startverb uv run ty check src/\stopverb}}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Reference: uv Commands}
\pre{\startverb
| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `uv init` | Create new project |
| `uv init --package` | Create distributable package |
| `uv add <pkg>` | Add dependency |
| `uv add --group dev <pkg>` | Add to dependency group |
| `uv remove <pkg>` | Remove dependency |
| `uv sync` | Install dependencies |
| `uv sync --all-groups` | Install all dependency groups |
| `uv run <cmd>` | Run command in venv |
| `uv run --with <pkg> <cmd>` | Run with temporary dependency |
| `uv build` | Build package |
| `uv publish` | Publish to PyPI |
\stopverb}

\subtree{
\title{Ad-hoc Dependencies with \code{\startverb --with\stopverb}}
\p{Use \code{\startverb uv run --with\stopverb} for one-off commands that need packages not in your project:}

\pre{\startverb
# Run Python with a temporary package
uv run --with requests python -c "import requests; print(requests.get('https://httpbin.org/ip').json())"

# Run a module with temporary deps
uv run --with rich python -m rich.progress

# Multiple packages
uv run --with requests --with rich python script.py

# Combine with project deps (adds to existing venv)
uv run --with httpx pytest  # project deps + httpx
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{When to use \code{\startverb --with\stopverb} vs \code{\startverb uv add\stopverb}:}}

\ul{
\li{\code{\startverb uv add\stopverb}: Package is a project dependency (goes in pyproject.toml/uv.lock)}
\li{\code{\startverb --with\stopverb}: One-off usage, testing, or scripts outside a project context}
}

\p{See [uv-commands.md](./references/uv-commands.md) for complete reference.}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Quick Reference: Dependency Groups}
\pre{\startverb
[dependency-groups]
dev = ["ruff", "ty"]
test = ["pytest", "pytest-cov", "hypothesis"]
docs = ["sphinx", "myst-parser"]
\stopverb}

\p{Install with: \code{\startverb uv sync --group dev --group test\stopverb}}
}

\subtree{
\title{Best Practices Checklist}
\ul{
\li{[ ] Use \code{\startverb src/\stopverb} layout for packages}
\li{[ ] Set \code{\startverb requires-python = ">=3.11"\stopverb}}
\li{[ ] Configure ruff with \code{\startverb select = ["ALL"]\stopverb} and explicit ignores}
\li{[ ] Use ty for type checking}
\li{[ ] Enforce test coverage minimum (80\%+)}
\li{[ ] Use dependency groups instead of extras for dev tools}
\li{[ ] Add \code{\startverb uv.lock\stopverb} to version control}
\li{[ ] Use PEP 723 for standalone scripts}
}
}

